   PIL/Pillow library

  Pillow is the modern, actively maintained fork of the original Python Imaging Library (PIL). It's the go-to library for image processing in Python, providing extensive file format support and a rich set of image manipulation capabilities.

PIL was created by Fredrik Lundh in 1995 but its development stalled around 2009 (last release: PIL 1.1.7). The community forked it as Pillow, which became the de facto replacement. You install Pillow but import it as PIL — the namespace stayed the same for backward compatibility.

